  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released 08/15/2022 at 11:30pm CT</p><h3 id=\"id-1.18.9-MinorChanges\">Minor Changes</h3><ul><li><p>Cleaned up the ticket label format, so that certain text fields fit better when printing</p></li><li><p>Setting up the Square integration no longer pulls in locations that are inactive</p></li><li><p>Improved the usability of the &quot;Appointment Statuses&quot; page</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"id-1.18.9-BugFixes\">Bug Fixes</h3><ul><li><p>Checking or unchecking the &quot;Skip customer receipt preference&quot; option for a Square terminal now saves properly</p></li><li><p>Resolved an issue where customer profile information was not being saved properly</p></li><li><p>Adding backordered parts to a refurbishment ticket is now supported and no longer returns an error</p></li><li><p>When navigating between &quot;Notes&quot; and &quot;Custom Forms&quot; within a new ticket, custom forms no longer disappear</p></li><li><p>Updating a trade-in layaway ticket no longer retroactively updates related items that had already been refurbished and sold back to &quot;Instock&quot;</p></li><li><p>Serialized backorder items will no longer prevent a ticket with other items attached from being saved</p></li><li><p>Customer referrals now reflect properly</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue where submitting inventory counts would return an error about &quot;Location ID&quot; and &quot;Created By&quot; fields being blank</p></li><li><p>Resolved some email and text notifications errors, which would cause the notifications to get stuck in &quot;New&quot; status</p></li><li><p>Diagnostic notes on a Return Repair ticket no longer overwrite diagnostic notes on the original repair ticket</p></li><li><p>Fixed an issue that was preventing a user from starting a return from the ticket list under the customer profile</p></li><li><p>Inventory for inactive locations will no longer appear in search inventory results</p></li></ul>",
      "representation": "export_view",
